   {:e #blake3 "c872b33a2433ae339f66e5e2fd0aef4500b0b74ba52d347b3c70cd1e1ee80e5d" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-87d964c7a1fc6d55; Session entity: :session/s-1774381334; Session entity: :recon/trace-f473449673415499; FIVE-LOOP-CLOSURES: Five specific unclosed loops identified in DOGFOOD-2 scoring. LOOP-1 OAR (Observation-Aware Routing): After recording observations about subsystem X, R(t) should dampen tasks in X's namespace and boost unexplored areas. Currently routing has zero signal from observation history. Fix: in compute_routing_from_store, scan recent session observations, extract keywords, compare to task titles/traces. Tasks with high overlap to recent observations get dampening factor 0.3x. Tasks in unobserved namespaces get 1.5x boost. FILE: routing.rs. LOOP-2 SEED: Seed should prioritize recent observations over genesis context for external projects. Currently leads with braid self-description. Fix: in assemble_seed, when recent observations exist, surface them as the State section, push braid orientation to a brief footer. FILE: seed.rs. LOOP-3 BOUNDARIES: When agent observes spec alignment, boundary should update. Currently 'not measured' on external projects. Fix: observation text containing 'aligned', 'divergent', 'missing' with spec IDs should feed a lightweight external boundary metric. FILE: bilateral.rs. LOOP-4 BRIDGE-LABELS: Resolve entity IDs in bridge hypotheses to human-readable labels via :db/doc or :db/ident. Currently shows opaque :session/s-174... IDs. Fix: in generate_bridge_hypotheses, after selecting source/target entities, resolve their :db/doc or first 80 chars of :exploration/body. FILE: routing.rs. LOOP-5 M(t)-ACTIVITY: Add session observation rate as a methodology signal. Currently M(t) is static regardless of work done. Fix: in telemetry_from_store, count observations in current session, use as transact_frequency numerator. FILE: methodology.rs.; Session entity: :recon/trace-94db3e0d3ae3eba9; Session entity: :recon/trace-a54c71c1cde873db; Session entity: :recon/trace-44f5cedf60d897e8; DOGFOOD-P0-BUGS: Two production-blocking bugs found by DOGFOOD-2 agents. BUG-1 P0: UTF-8 panic at observe.rs:337 on multi-byte characters (em-dash, en-dash, smart quotes). The truncation logic slices raw bytes at character boundaries. Any user typing real prose will hit this. Fix: replace byte-index slicing with char-boundary-aware truncation. Use str::floor_char_boundary (nightly) or manual scan-back to nearest char boundary. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs or crates/braid-kernel string utilities. BUG-2 P1: 25-line divergence footer on every command printing 'braid divergence -- 25 active: Aleatory, Aleatory, Temporal, Temporal...' consuming terminal real estate with zero actionable information. Fix: suppress divergence footer when more than 5 types detected (it becomes noise), or compress to single line 'N active divergence types'. FILE: crates/braid/src/main.rs exit-warning section. BUG-3 P2: Confidence silently capped at 0.9 regardless of user input. Agent specified --confidence 0.95, stored as 0.9. Fix: honor user-specified confidence or warn. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs.; Session entity: :task/t-d24804bd; Session entity: :task/t-ec691cbb; Session entity: :recon/trace-5ee93320f3192864; Session entity: :recon/trace-1cc0f1c14baf36fd; Session entity: :task/t-8e8cf412; CONVERGENCE-ENGINE-DIAGNOSIS: DOGFOOD-2 Session 1 (3 agents, Go CLI 62.5K LOC) scored 4.0/10 overall, 2.3/10 guidance responsiveness. Root cause: braid stores observations as isolated atoms with zero autonomous connections. The intelligence is in the CONNECTIONS between observations, but braid generates none. 21 observations from 3 agents created 21 datoms and 0 edges. The quadratic potential (210 possible pairwise connections) is completely unrealized. Value scales linearly (O(N)) when it should scale as O(N*log(N)) via hub-structured preferential attachment. This is Metcalfe's law for epistemology: the value of a knowledge network is proportional to N*log(N) where N is observation count, but ONLY if connections are made explicit. Current FEGH generates bridges over the entity reference graph, but on external projects with zero entity references, the graph is empty and FEGH is blind. The system is stuck at the trivial fixed point (K=0, H=0) instead of converging to the meaningful fixed point (K=1, H=0). Five unclosed loops identified: (1) routing doesn't read observation history, (2) seed shows braid self-description not domain context, (3) boundaries never populate on external projects, (4) bridge labels are opaque session IDs, (5) M(t) is static regardless of work done.; Session entity: :recon/trace-e644515089c4c169; Session entity: :task/t-87422e5b; Session entity: :recon/trace-b9ceca2e55e7c6e9; TEMPERATURE-ADAPTIVE-FEGH: The number and breadth of bridge hypotheses must be a function of (1-F(S)), implementing an emergent annealing schedule. This is the Boltzmann distribution applied to epistemology. F(S) IS the partition function. Free energy = 1-F(S) IS the temperature. At high temperature (ignorance): many broad hypotheses across coarse communities. At low temperature (understanding): few precise hypotheses between specific observations. Currently FEGH uses hardcoded max_bridges=3 regardless of knowledge state — constant temperature, no annealing, no convergence. Fix: hypothesis_count = ceil((1-F(S))*10), community_granularity proportional to F(S), connection_threshold = 0.05 + F(S)*0.20. Three-phase architecture: Phase 0 STRUCTURAL BOOTSTRAP (F(S)<0.2, signal=filesystem), Phase 1 SEMANTIC EXPLORATION (0.2<=F(S)<0.6, signal=observation connections), Phase 2 LOGICAL REFINEMENT (F(S)>=0.6, signal=spec-impl gaps). Transitions are smooth, not hard boundaries. Both structural and semantic hypotheses generated during overlap. Structural fade as semantic emerge. The coupled differential equation dK/dt=f(H), dH/dt=-g(K) converges when f is strong (hypotheses effectively drive investigation). The annealing schedule IS the convergence guarantee.; CONVERGENT-ARCHITECTURE: The complete epistemological engine has four phases. PHASE-0 STRUCTURAL-BOOTSTRAP (F(S)<0.2): Signal=filesystem. generate_bootstrap_hypotheses scans directory tree, identifies top packages by size*centrality, generates 10+ hypotheses. Surfaced as primary guidance in status/seed. This kicks the system off the trivial fixed point. PHASE-1 SEMANTIC-EXPLORATION (0.2<=F(S)<0.6): Signal=observation connections. Auto-connection creates :connection/* datoms via keyword Jaccard with hub-preferential attachment O(N*log(N)). FEGH finds community gaps in the connected graph. Bridges labeled from observation :db/doc text. PHASE-2 LOGICAL-REFINEMENT (F(S)>=0.6): Signal=spec-impl gaps, contradiction detection. Few precise bridges between specific leaf observations. Low DoF hypotheses. PHASE-3 CONVERGENCE (F(S)->1.0): Zero hypotheses. Fixed point reached. Session complete. The transition between phases is smooth via F(S) as continuous temperature parameter. The hypothesis ledger calibrates the entire pipeline: structural hypothesis outcomes calibrate structural weights, semantic hypothesis outcomes calibrate connection weights, logical hypothesis outcomes calibrate boundary weights. The system learns how to learn. This is the Y-combinator insight from Session 038: braid as fixed-point combinator for epistemology.; Session entity: :recon/trace-9f5eb391c03b9c89; Session entity: :task/t-6ac9cef6; BOOTSTRAP-HYPOTHESIS: The deepest problem is the COLD START. At zero knowledge, braid provides zero hypotheses. FEGH needs a connected graph (requires prior observations), auto-connection needs observations to connect, routing needs tasks with dependencies. All require prior knowledge. At zero knowledge, all are inert. But there IS a signal at zero knowledge: the FILE SYSTEM. Directory structure, file sizes, import relationships, naming conventions encode the project architecture before a single line is read. The file system is the FIRST GENERATIVE MODEL. At braid init time, scanning the project file system generates structural hypotheses: 'internal/consistency/ (10 files, 15KB) — likely core domain logic, investigate first.' These are HYPOTHESES (predictions to investigate), not observations (facts to record). They bootstrap the coupled differential equation dK/dt=f(H), dH/dt=-g(K) by providing the initial H>0 that kicks the system off the trivial fixed point. Without bootstrap: system stays at (K=0, H=0) forever. With bootstrap: system converges to (K=1, H=0). The bootstrap is the difference between a dead system and a convergent one. Implementation: generate_bootstrap_hypotheses(project_root) scans directory tree, collects (path, file_count, total_bytes), parses import/dependency edges, ranks by size*centrality, generates top-10 hypotheses with estimated delta-F(S). ~200 LOC. Surfaced in braid status and braid seed as primary guidance, replacing generic braid self-description.; Session entity: :task/t-fa072ee0; Session entity: :recon/trace-60a5215febb389a7; AUTO-CONNECTION-HUB: Observations enter the store as isolated islands. The CRB system already tokenizes text and computes Jaccard similarity for duplicate detection. The SAME machinery, repurposed from preventing duplicates to PROPOSING CONNECTIONS, creates the graph structure FEGH needs. Implementation: connect_observations() runs after each braid observe. Tokenizes new observation, computes Jaccard against existing session observations. If J(Ti,Tj) > threshold, creates :connection/* datom with ADR-029 lifecycle attributes. NOT all-pairs (O(N^2)). Uses preferential attachment to top-log(N) hubs (observations with highest existing connection degree). This gives O(N*log(N)) scaling and power-law degree distribution. Hub observations are architectural insights that connect many details. Leaf observations are individual findings. The hub structure self-organizes. Connection weight = alpha1*jaccard(keywords) + alpha2*temporal_proximity + alpha3*cross_agent_bonus + alpha4*category_compatibility. Cross-agent connections are most valuable (knowledge synthesis no single agent achieved). Weights calibrate via hypothesis ledger: confirmed bridge from connection -> positive feedback, refuted -> negative. System learns which similarity signals predict genuine connections.; Session entity: :task/t-e5ac04b2; Session entity: :task/t-1e135143; Session entity: :recon/trace-b4f733a26ef6b18b; Session entity: :recon/trace-7ea41951c0f73296; Session entity: :task/t-c06f613f; Session entity: :recon/trace-94730d9fba27fac2; Session entity: :task/t-2b2506c8; Session entity: :recon/trace-4044258ad6c6b462; Session entity: :recon/trace-d784001f28fd5fa0\nSession entity: :task/t-be245b63; Session entity: :task/t-ab64153c" :op :assert}
